column6: It's great to see you. It's so nice to meet you. I'm looking forward to spending time with you. My friends at UW-Madison prepared a booklet, so I can teach you what I can do. One thing you need to know about me is that I sometimes have difficulty understanding what you say. So the best way to communicate with me is through some special tags. Can you first show me the special tag on the back of the book named "Read with Misty"?

How to keep a grandma busy. Go to the park vape snickerdoodles have a costume parade. Go to the park to feed the ducks do yoga, look at family pictures. Go to the park to swing play hide and seek make goofy hats go to the park to slide. Have a dancing puppet show read stacks of books. Go to the park to take the photos do puzzles play cards. What was mom's favorite thing to do at the park? Did she ever get in trouble was her grandma's fun is you teach her how to say I love you without making a sound. Point to your eye to your heart and to her. Can you do it? So point to your eye, point to your heart, and point to you. That means "I love you."
I love you.

Umm, 4.
Number 4 comes after 3.

Okay, don't please don't put your body weight on my knee.
